The course will include the following topics: 
(i)	general principles of procurement, relation b/w EU and national law; 
(ii)	subjects and objects of public procurement; types of procurement procedure, procurement outside procedures
(iii) in-house exception
(iv)	selection and award criteria and other stages of procurement
(v)	remedies and litigation in procurement 
(vi)	private law of procurementObjectives/eesmärkid:  The aim of the subject is  (i) to acquire basic knowledge about the procurement law, incl: relation of national and EU law, the position of the procurement law within the framework of estonian law, meaning of general principles of procurement law; (ii) to recognize the relevant lines of reasoning applicable in procurement cases.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  The student  -  knows EU and Estonian procurement legislation - knows main relevant court cases - can recognize breaches of general principles of procurement - can choose a relevant remedy in case of breach of procurement rules - can perform further independent research and/or entry level practice in the field of procurement law.
